# Playwright Java - Page Object Model (POM) Skill

## Project Stack Assumptions
- **Language**: Java 11+
- **Library**: Playwright for Java (`com.microsoft.playwright`)
- **Pattern**: Page Object Model
- **Assertions**: AssertJ (`org.assertj.core.api.Assertions`)
- **Location**: `src/test/java/pages/`

---

## Base Page Class (Always Extend This)

```java
package pages;

import com.microsoft.playwright.Page;

public abstract class BasePage {

    protected final Page page;

    public BasePage(Page page) {
        this.page = page;
    }

    public void navigateTo(String url) {
        page.navigate(url);
    }

    public String getTitle() {
        return page.title();
    }

    public void waitForPageLoad() {
        page.waitForLoadState();
    }
}
```

---

## Page Object Template

```java
package pages;

import com.microsoft.playwright.Page;
import com.microsoft.playwright.Locator;

public class LoginPage extends BasePage {

    // --- Locators (define at top as constants) ---
    private static final String USERNAME_INPUT = "#username";
    private static final String PASSWORD_INPUT = "#password";
    private static final String LOGIN_BUTTON   = "button[type='submit']";
    private static final String ERROR_MESSAGE  = ".error-message";
    private static final String DASHBOARD_HEADER = "h1.dashboard-title";

    public LoginPage(Page page) {
        super(page);
    }

    // --- Navigation ---
    public void navigateTo() {
        page.navigate("https://yourapp.com/login");
    }

    // --- Actions ---
    public void enterUsername(String username) {
        page.fill(USERNAME_INPUT, username);
    }

    public void enterPassword(String password) {
        page.fill(PASSWORD_INPUT, password);
    }

    public void clickLoginButton() {
        page.click(LOGIN_BUTTON);
    }

    public void login(String username, String password) {
        enterUsername(username);
        enterPassword(password);
        clickLoginButton();
    }

    // --- Assertions / Getters ---
    public boolean isDashboardVisible() {
        return page.isVisible(DASHBOARD_HEADER);
    }

    public String getErrorMessage() {
        return page.textContent(ERROR_MESSAGE);
    }

    public boolean isErrorDisplayed() {
        return page.isVisible(ERROR_MESSAGE);
    }
}
```

