## Page Object Rules
- ✅ One class per page / major component
- ✅ All locators defined as private static final Strings at the top
- ✅ Action methods return `void`, getter methods return values
- ✅ Extend `BasePage`
- ✅ No assertions inside page objects — assertions go in step definitions
- ❌ No hardcoded waits (`Thread.sleep`) — use Playwright's auto-wait
- ❌ No test logic inside page objects

---

## Naming Conventions
| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Class | PascalCase + "Page" | `CheckoutPage.java` |
| Locator constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `SUBMIT_BUTTON` |
| Action methods | camelCase verb | `clickSubmitButton()` |
| Getter methods | camelCase `get/is` | `getErrorMessage()`, `isModalOpen()` |

